{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6d957c1c-9125-4b3a-b5f2-bbab704af49b","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net 2.9.3 project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Remove the old runner package:**\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n```\n\n**2. Add the MTP runner package:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.5.0\" />\n```\n\n**3. Enable MTP in your project file:**\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**4. Run tests:**\n```bash\ndotnet test          # still works\ndotnet run           # now also works (test project becomes executable)\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit` 2.9.3 is compatible — no version change needed.\n- The `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform` property switches the SDK plumbing. Without it, `dotnet test` falls back to VSTest.\n- If you use `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`, keep it — it's still required.\n- For CI, `dotnet test --no-build` works the same way.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"671f31ca-8020-4036-9a45-6906d04345b4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":375},"id":"8ed39098-04ff-400c-aaf4-cfa9abbaf46f","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:47.885Z","parentId":"b68e631c-d317-4333-b551-c4a4a09dfa64"}
